No!

33:45.324 --> 33:47.157
- [laughing]
- Shut up!

33:53.632 --> 33:55.565
- [snorts]
- [laughs]

33:55.567 --> 33:58.101
[buzzing]

33:58.103 --> 33:59.169
[squeals]

34:05.511 --> 34:07.377
I'm gonna go get
some more blankets

34:07.379 --> 34:10.679
so we can make a fort
and stay safe, okay?

34:14.620 --> 34:16.686
- Dr. Miller.
- Hi. Nice to finally meet you.

34:29.601 --> 34:32.302
She likes sitting here,
and she likes it dark.

34:32.304 --> 34:35.237
Why would she like it in here?
It smells like vomit.

34:44.616 --> 34:47.350
She's got something like seaweed
growing out of her scalp.

34:47.351 --> 34:49.553
Really? What do you mean?

34:49.554 --> 34:52.489
I don't know what it is.

34:52.491 --> 34:54.623
I'm not gonna cut it
until we do.

34:54.626 --> 34:58.161
She has clearly
been traumatized.

34:58.163 --> 35:00.397
Let's at least give her--

35:06.738 --> 35:08.605
[gasping]

35:08.607 --> 35:10.707
[thunder rumbling]

35:17.649 --> 35:19.349
SANDRA: All right, Linda,

35:19.351 --> 35:21.551
would you like to finish
what you were saying?

35:27.459 --> 35:30.227
- We should watch real cable.
- That asshole security guard...

35:30.229 --> 35:32.762
- We're all adults here.
- is a certifiable psychotic.

35:32.764 --> 35:35.298
We don't need cartoons from
the '40s to calm us down.

35:35.300 --> 35:37.767
- I saw him dragging Natasha...
- Where has Natasha been anyway?

35:37.769 --> 35:40.203
Okay, okay, I cannot hear

35:40.205 --> 35:42.672
