- [thunderclap]

35:59.324 --> 36:01.625
Would you like to finish
what you were saying?

36:01.627 --> 36:04.294
[girls cheering]

36:04.296 --> 36:05.762
Okay, okay.

36:05.764 --> 36:08.765
I know that they flicker,
but they never go off.

36:12.771 --> 36:14.838
[thunder rumbling]

36:14.840 --> 36:17.674
Okay, the lights flicker,
but they never go out.

36:17.676 --> 36:19.776
- [girls laugh]
- I'm freaking out.

36:19.778 --> 36:20.844
Who's hungry?

36:33.725 --> 36:35.725
Hey, can we all be quiet?

36:35.727 --> 36:38.495
She's trying to say something.

36:38.497 --> 36:40.864
- Hey, hey, hey, you guys...
- [thunder rumbling]

36:44.836 --> 36:47.470
I'm sorry. Her signing
is really cryptic.

36:47.472 --> 36:49.706
I can't understand
her hand articulation.

36:49.708 --> 36:51.775
Can you slow it down, please?

36:54.546 --> 36:55.879
She's saying
there's a girl in this room

36:55.881 --> 36:58.348
that none of us can see.

37:02.421 --> 37:05.288
I see her.
Tell her I can see her too.

37:05.290 --> 37:07.490
Ask her if she can see
Becky's eight-year-old twin

37:07.492 --> 37:09.292
standing by her, always
asking her for his blanket.

37:09.294 --> 37:11.861
What the fuck?
What the fuck? How--

37:11.863 --> 37:14.431
How the fuck did you know
that this was his blanket?

37:14.433 --> 37:16.766
She says she doesn't
belong here.

37:16.768 --> 37:19.569
Join the sorority, sister.
None of us belong here.

37:19.571 --> 37:20.570
Hey.
[snaps fingers]

37:20.572 --> 37:22.706
Come out of it.

37:22.708 --> 37:24.908
MILLER: Belongs to the water?

37:24.910 --> 37:27.544
Ask her why
she learned to sign.

37:32.417 --> 37:36.319
Pirates? Pirates?

37:36.321 --> 37:38.388
- Huh.
- Sign language pirates.

37:38.390 --> 37:39.856
Don't interrupt
the process, London.

37:39.858 --> 37:41.658
What do you care anyway,
Sandra?

37:41.660 --> 37:43.660
You're just gonna
leave us soon anyway.

37:43.662 --> 37:44.861
Who told you that?

37:44.863 --> 37:47.731
